citRespParty.rpOrgName: Government of the republic of Maldives

dataIdInfo.idAbs: The dataset represents the administrative level 2 (island, atoll, city) of Maldives

Consts.useLimit: See the COD/FOD Registry Terms of Use. This does not replace any terms of use information provided with the dataset.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following was found and fixed by ITOS: 1. 123 of the Admin2 units had their Admin2 name duplicated in the EN Admin0 name field. This error is corrected so that they all have the name “Maldives”. 2. 131 of the Admin2 units had “N” as their ADM0_DV name, 3 had “Y”. This error is corrected so that they all have the name “ދިވެހިރާއްޖޭގެ ޖުމްހޫރިއްޔާ”. 3. 123 of the Admin2 units had a unique Dhivehi name in the Admin0 pcode field. This error is corrected so that they all have the pcode “MV”. 4. Found and fixed 11 overlap errors and 4 gap errors.
The following was found by ITOS but is not addressed in this version: 1. 8 administrative level 2 islands have duplicate names within their administrative level 1 atoll. Within administrative level 1 atoll “Gaafu Dhaalu” [MV017] these are: two administrative level 2 islands called “Aakirahuttaa” [MV017014] and [MV017015], three islands called “Bodehuttaa” [MV017021], [MV017022], and [MV017023], three called “Dhoonirehaa” [MV017009], [MV017038] and [MV017039], two called “Haveyyerataa” [MV017067] and [MV017068], and two called “Maarehaa” [MV017141] and [MV017142].
Within atoll “Laamu” [MV015] these are two called “Bodufinolhu” [MV015018] and [MV015019] and two called “Boduhuraa” [MV015020] and [MV015021].
Finally, within atoll “Gaafu Alifu” [MV016] there are two called “Maadhigavara” [MV016083] and [MV016084]. 2. Two Admin2 units fall outside of their attributed Admin1: "LD1341" and "Farukolhufushi". UNOCHA has instructed ITOS to keep attribution as-is
